## 16. 30-second recap

There are three main PMO types: **Supportive, Controlling, and Directive**. They differ mainly in **how much authority and control they exercise**. A Supportive PMO enables, a Controlling PMO enforces, and a Directive PMO directly manages. The best choice depends on organizational culture, project maturity, project complexity, and strategic importance. In many cases, a **hybrid PMO model** is the most effective solution. 

